    {
      "id": "171c3c6adff70872c67db10e1e0b4943d7eff5be",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2014-07-08 19:52:05.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2: Code-Review-1\n\n(1 comment)\n\nSorry, I don't think this is correct.  LIBCFS_ALLOC*() itself doesn't set __GFP_ZERO that I can see.  There is OBD_ALLOC*() that is used in lustre/ code that sets __GFP_ZERO, but the LIBCFS_ALLOC_*() calls do not expect the memory to be zeroed.\n\nThat said, it would be better to change these LIBCFS_ALLOC() calls to LIBCFS_ALLOC_GFP(..., GFP_NOFS | __GFP_ZERO) instead of calling memset() afterward.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "cd1eae893ba5f03f101c35142966fd2bd65f5bb4",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 302,
        "name": "Patrick Farrell",
        "email": "paf@cray.com",
        "username": "paf",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2014-07-08 19:58:36.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2: -Code-Review\n\nAndreas,\n\nTake a look at #define LIBCFS_ALLOC_POST(ptr, size)                                        \\\n\nI may be reading this incorrectly, but as I understand it:\nLIBCFS_ALLOC becomes:\n        LIBCFS_ALLOC_GFP(ptr, size, GFP_NOFS) or LIBCFS_ALLOC_GFP(ptr, size, 0)\n\nAnd LIBCFS_ALLOC_GFP uses LIBCFS_ALLOC_POST, which zeroes the allocated memory.\n\nThe only exception is the !__KERNEL__ version of LIBCFS_ALLOC_GFP, which I believe is effectively deprecated.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "dcaf22bc7dc5f728f9125e1cb1466ffb2b409ffc",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 419,
        "name": "Frank Zago",
        "email": "fzago@cray.com",
        "username": "fzago.cray"
      },
      "date": "2014-07-08 20:00:49.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nLIBCFS_ALLOC_GFP in !KERNEL case is also using calloc(), so no problem either.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "f233080490c8ec420087cdad676f008b5db5d278",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2014-07-08 21:24:23.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nIn this case, it would be better to change the LIBCFS_ALLOC() code to pass __GFP_ZERO to kmalloc() or vzalloc() instead of having an explicit memset() in LIBCFS_POST().",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
